    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Royal Institution of Great Britain</hi></placeName>
                    <date>8<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> March.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I wrote to your friend immediately, saw him, talked to him, and liked him. I thought he would probably tell you all this—otherwise I would have written to you.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>The subjects on which he spoke to me have often occupied my attention.</p>
<p>Yours ever | John Tyndall</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7552.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Tyndall, 7 March [1871]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Tyndall refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3579.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Ogle</ref>. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7552.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Tyndall, 7 March [1871]</ref> and n. 2.</note>
        </div>        
            
